CanvasComments.BodyText: Creates new entries for the DataPortal. WARNING: This will ERASE existing data!
Adds children objects to the DataPortal

There is no * selector in Entity SQL. In order to select all the fields, you must manually specify them. The names of these fields and containers can easily be found in the Excel file you used to create the DataPortal.
Select the DataPortalQuery DataPortal for each DataPortal Sync and Query module.

Description: This DataFlow adds data to a DataPortal and then attempts to query it.

ModuleInputs.Description: SQL query to perform against tables
ModuleInputs.Name: Query
ModuleInputs.ValueObj:
SELECT DISTINCT
	cases.FamilyHistoryId AS ParentInstanceId,
    familyhistoryentries.*
FROM [t0] cases JOIN [t1] familyhistoryentries ON cases.RowId = familyhistoryentries.RowId
UNION
SELECT DISTINCT
	cases.FamilyHistoryId AS ParentInstanceId,
    familyhistoryentries.*
FROM [t0] cases JOIN [t2] familyhistoryentries ON cases.RowId = familyhistoryentries.RowId

ModuleInputs.Description: The query to execute. Note that if you select an entire object using VALUE, any related pages/tables will not be returned. To select items from other tables/pages, join them.
ModuleInputs.Name: Query
ModuleInputs.ValueObj:
SELECT
c.Name,
c.Food,
c.Foods,
c.Decimal,
c.Double,
c.UniqueIdentifier,
b.FirstName,
b.LastName,
b.DOB,
b.Product,
b.PolicyCreatedDate,
b.Gender,
b.OptyId,
b.InsuredFullYear,
f.HasFamilyHistory,
f.FamHistoryEntries
FROM Cases AS c
JOIN FamilyHistories AS f 
ON c.Id = f.CaseId
JOIN Basics AS b
ON c.Id = b.CaseId
WHERE f.HasFamilyHistory = @hasFamilyHistory
ORDER BY c.Id
